properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued March 2 at 9:35AM MST until March 3 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect until 5 AM MST Tuesday.

* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph
expected. Areas of blowing snow will make further travel impacts
along Interstate 80 and 25.

* WHERE...The southern Laramie Range, including the I-80 Summit.

* WHEN...Until 5 AM MST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel will be difficult
especially for lightweight, high profile vehicles and campers.
Blowing snow will create areas of low to limited visibility
along with slick to snow-covered roadways.
properties.instruction:
People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown
around or damaged by the wind.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM MST TUESDAY
